### 2. Robust Room Management
- **Room Validation:** Implemented a `/check_room` backend endpoint. Users can no longer join arbitrary rooms; they must enter a valid 6-character code generated by a host.
- **Race Condition Fixed:** The server now tracks created rooms immediately, ensuring that clients can join even before the host connects their WebSocket.
- **Dynamic Connection:** Integrated a centralized [jam-core.js](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/airplay%202/jam-core.js) to manage WebSocket connections and shared state across all player pages.

### 6. Bi-directional Audio Sync
- **Cross-Instrument Sound:** Piano players now automatically load and play drum samples when their partner hits a drum. Drum players now have a built-in synth to play back piano notes.
- **WebSocket Fix:** Corrected a port conflict that was preventing player pages from connecting to the jam server.

### 5. Player Connection Feedback
- **Join/Leave Toasts:** The app now automatically displays a toast notification (e.g., "Player joined: anonymous") when someone enters or leaves your jam room.
- **Improved UX:** You no longer have to wonder if your partner is connected; the system provides immediate visual feedback.
